cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.AL 

This paper is primarily focused on network virtualization and the Virtual Network Embedding (VNE) problem, which is a key issue in the field of computer networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves algorithm design and analysis, which suggests it could also fit into cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AL (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper proposes customized algorithms for specific network topologies, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
